The paper focuses on learning rich representations for vision tasks, specifically semantic segmentation and category-level semantic segmentation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural architectures such as ResNet, DenseNet, and NASNet, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also mentions the use of data-driven regularization functions, which could fall under the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of a feedforward multilayer network, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
